This paper deals with traffic regulation in computer networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer networking (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the mathematical theory behind traffic regulators, which involves concepts from information theory (cs.IT) and control systems (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper discusses the performance of the regulator in terms of worst-case delay, which is a security concern and could fall under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper discusses the application of the regulator to interleaved systems, which could fall under the category of parallel and distributed computing (cs.PF).
